@@TJvGenetic.CrossoverProbability
Description:
This property is the probability of crossover (By default, 0.6). The crossover is used during the reproduction. if you have a gene xxxxxx and another one oooooo, the new gene, after a cross over is xxxxoo. if this property is 1.0 or higher, it will cross over each time. if this property is 0.0, it will never cross over.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvGenetic.Generation
Description:
This ReadOnly property is the current Generation Level. This property is reseted when you call the NewGeneration method and incremented when you call the NextGeneration Method.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvGenetic.MemberSize
Description:
This property is the size, in byte, of the Members. After a change of this property, you have to call the NewGeneration method. You can't call the NextGeneration after a modification of this property, cause all members are freed !.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvGenetic.MutateProbability
Description:
This property is the probability of mutation (by default 0.003). The mutation is used during the reproduction. A gene 00010001 after a mutation on the third bit would become 00110001. You shouldn't put a Value above 0.1, or the result may become unstable.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvGenetic.Numbers
Description:
This property is the number of members you want. After a change of this property, you have to call the NewGeneration method. You can't call the NextGeneration after a modification of this property, cause all members are freed !.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvGenetic.OnTestMember
Description:
This event is called when a member has been generated (randomly or by reproduction). if this event is not Assigned when you call the NewGeneration or NextGeneration method, you'll receive an Exception.

